        "cooked": "<p>Thanks for the report! This is possibly a reproduction of this bug:</p>\n<aside class=\"onebox githubissue\" data-onebox-src=\"https://github.com/apple/foundationdb/issues/895\">\n  <header class=\"source\">\n\n      <a href=\"https://github.com/apple/foundationdb/issues/895\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">github.com/apple/foundationdb</a>\n  </header>\n\n  <article class=\"onebox-body\">\n    <div class=\"github-row\">\n  <div class=\"github-icon-container\" title=\"Issue\">\n\t  <svg width=\"60\" height=\"60\" class=\"github-icon\" viewBox=\"0 0 14 16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M7 2.3c3.14 0 5.7 2.56 5.7 5.7s-2.56 5.7-5.7 5.7A5.71 5.71 0 0 1 1.3 8c0-3.14 2.56-5.7 5.7-5.7zM7 1C3.14 1 0 4.14 0 8s3.14 7 7 7 7-3.14 7-7-3.14-7-7-7zm1 3H6v5h2V4zm0 6H6v2h2v-2z\"></path></svg>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"github-info-container\">\n    <h4>\n      <a href=\"https://github.com/apple/foundationdb/issues/895\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Mutating a directory multiple times simultaneously in the same transaction is unsafe</a>\n    </h4>\n\n    <div class=\"github-info\">\n      <div class=\"date\">\n        opened <span class=\"discourse-local-date\" data-format=\"ll\" data-date=\"2018-11-04\" data-time=\"18:37:57\" data-timezone=\"UTC\">06:37PM - 04 Nov 18 UTC</span>\n      </div>\n\n\n      <div class=\"user\">\n        <a href=\"https://github.com/jared2501\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n          <img alt=\"jared2501\" src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/foundationdb/original/2X/b/bac8d3f100b758ccf04166f1bea7d10ac6d57434.png\" class=\"onebox-avatar-inline\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" data-dominant-color=\"D9E7CB\">\n          jared2501\n        </a>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"labels\">\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n  <div class=\"github-row\">\n    <p class=\"github-body-container\">The Java implementation of DirectoryLayer does not seem to work when used with a<span class=\"show-more-container\"><a href=\"\" rel=\"noopener\" class=\"show-more\">\u2026</a></span><span class=\"excerpt hidden\">n FDBTransaction, but does when used with an FDBDatabase.\n\nI'm seeing issues where the DirectoryLayer allocates a prefix and returns it to me. I commit the transaction successfully, but future calls to the DirectoryLayer from new transactions do not find the allocated directory.\n\nIf I use a FDBDatabase when invoking DirectoryLayer.createOrOpen(...) then all works fine.\n\nSince FDBTransaction implements TransactionContext I would have expected it to work with DirectoryLayer. Is this a correct assumption? I know this issue is not the most helpful, but I'm not quite sure where to start on getting useful information.</span></p>\n  </div>\n\n  </article>\n\n  <div class=\"onebox-metadata\">\n    \n    \n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"clear: both\"></div>\n</aside>\n\n<p>Unfortunately at this point, I don\u2019t think there has been any attempt to make these directory operations within a single transaction thread safe.</p>",
